\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Offaly_GAA\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.8042120260507823e-19, \"text\": \"Offaly\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Offaly_GAA\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Offaly_GAA\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"her spot\", \"from\": 835, \"to\": 843}, {\"ngram\": \"Walsh\", \"from\": 867, \"to\": 872}, {\"ngram\": \"an agonising 3-2 split decision\", \"from\": 881, \"to\": 912}, {\"ngram\": \"the judges\", \"from\": 918, \"to\": 928}, {\"ngram\": \"some observers\", \"from\": 935, \"to\": 949}, {\"ngram\": \"the scoring\", \"from\": 966, \"to\": 977}]}, {\"sentence\": \"In the second round, Rygielska received a standing eight count from the referee, yet three of the five judges awarded the round to the Pole.\", \"from\": 980, \"to\": 1120, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the second round\", \"from\": 983, \"to\": 999}, {\"ngram\": \"Rygielska\", \"from\": 1001, \"to\": 1010}, {\"ngram\": \"a standing eight count\", \"from\": 1020, \"to\": 1042}, {\"ngram\": \"the referee\", \"from\": 1048, \"to\": 1059}, {\"ngram\": \"the five judges\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1089}, {\"ngram\": \"the round\", \"from\": 1098, \"to\": 1107}, {\"ngram\": \"the Pole\", \"from\": 1111, \"to\": 1119}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Rygielska was also docked a point for holding but while the Norwegian and Sri Lankan judges deemed Walsh the clear winner, awarding her a 29-27 victory, the Italian, Moroccan and Argentinian judges scored the fight 28-apiece, meaning that under professional rules, the fight would have been deemed a draw.\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1182, \"end\": 1191, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Norwegian_language\", \"score\": 0.626804983123939, \"rank\": 0.595244984442501, \"text\": \"Norwegian\", \"t